text.__SUMMARY__: Conus cazalisoi is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Conidae, the cone snails, cone shells or cones.This snail is predatory and venomous and is capable of "stinging" humans.
text.Distribution: This marine species of cone snail occurs off the Cape Verdes.
text.References: Cossignani T. & Fiadeiro R. (2018). Quattro nuovi coni da Capo Verde. Malacologia Mostra Mondiale. 98: 14-20.
